‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William d'Isney III was born about 1276, in Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William II d'Isney and Jane de Dive. He married Joan Langford in 1313, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1327, in his hometown, at the age of 52."},"et":{"Abt 1276–1327":"umbes 1276–1327","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1290–1328":"1290–1328","1313–1400":"1313–1400","–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1235":"1235","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"umbes 1276","1276":"1276","Abt. 1300":"umbes 1300","1293":"1293","1328":"1328","1290":"1290","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1276–1327":"noin 1276–1327","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1290–1328":"1290–1328","1313–1400":"1313–1400","–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1235":"1235","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"noin 1276","1276":"1276","Abt. 1300":"noin 1300","1293":"1293","1328":"1328","1290":"1290","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 12